      <section id="section-typeface" class="site-section">
        <h3 class="hca-text--title">Typeface</h3>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-6">
            <div class="site-container--body-content">
              <p class="hca-text--body-1">Open Sans is the chosen typeface for the HCA Design System. It is a free, open source, sans-serif font created and maintained by Google. It was developed with a focus on having a neutral, yet friendly appearance, and is optimized for legibility across print, web, and mobile interfaces.</p>
              <p class="hca-text--body-1">Open Sans is also one of the fastest loading fonts from <a href="https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Open+Sans" target="_blank">Google Fonts</a>.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-6">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-sm-12">
                <span class="hca-text--display-1 hca-text__weight--regular">ABCDEFGHIJKLMN<br />OPQRSTUVWXYZ<br />abcdefghijklmnop<br />qrstuvwxyz0123<br />456789</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="section-font-weights-used" class="site-section">
        <h3 class="hca-text--title">Font weights used</h3>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-6">
            <div class="site-container--body-content">
              <p class="hca-text--body-1">Our base typographic system utilizes the <span class="hca-text__weight--light">light (300)</span>, <span class="hca-text__weight--regular">regular (400)</span>, and <span class="hca-text__weight--semibold">semibold (600)</span> font weights that come baked right in to Open Sans.</p>
              <p class="hca-text--body-1">We stuck to just these three weights to avoid visual clutter and to lay the ground for a solid visual hierarchy when it comes to type.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-6">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-sm-12">
                <span class="hca-text--display-1 hca-text__weight--light">Open Sans Light</span>
                <span class="hca-text--display-1 hca-text__weight--regular">Open Sans Regular</span>
                <span class="hca-text--display-1 hca-text__weight--semibold">Open Sans Semibold</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>


      <section id="section-line-length-and-height" class="site-section">
        <h3 class="hca-text--title">Line Length &amp; Height</h3>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-6">
            {{!-- <h3 class="hca-text--body-2">Line Length</h3> --}}
            <div class="site-container--body-content">
              <p class="hca-text--body-1">Consider this advice on readability and line length from the Baymard Institute (a world leader in usability studies for Fortune 500 companies):</p>
              <p class="hca-text--body-1">“You should have around 60 characters per line if you want a good reading experience. Having the right amount of characters on each line is key to the readability of your text.”</p>
              <p class="hca-text--body-1">"Too wide – if a line of text is too long, the user’s eye will have a hard time focusing on the text. This is because the length makes it difficult to get an idea of where the line starts and ends. Furthermore it can be difficult to continue from the correct line in large blocks of text.”</p>
              <p class="hca-text--body-1">"Too narrow – if a line is too short, the eye will have to travel back too often, breaking the reader’s rhythm. Too short lines also tend to stress people, making them begin on the next line before finishing the current one (hence skipping potentially important words).”</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-6">
            {{!-- <h3 class="hca-text--body-2">Line Height</h3> --}}
            <div class="site-container--body-content">
              <p class="hca-text--body-1">To achieve proper readability and appropriate pacing, specific line heights have been determined based on each style’s individual size and weight. </p>
              <p class="hca-text--body-1">Line wrapping only applies to Body, Subhead, Headline, Display 1, and Display 2 styles. All other styles should exist as single lines.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-8">
            <figure class="hca-visual-example">
              <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/essentials/typography/body-line-length.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__example" alt="The ideal range for body copy is about 60 characters long before breaking to the next line." />
              <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-text--caption">The ideal range for body copy is about 60 characters long before breaking to the next line.</figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-8">
            <figure class="hca-visual-example">
              <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/essentials/typography/short-line-length.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__example" alt="The ideal range for short copy is 30-35 characters before breaking to the second line." />
              <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-text--caption">Short lines are copy that is not long enough to be a paragraph. The ideal range for short copy is 30-35 characters before breaking to the second line.</figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>
        </div>

      </section>
      {{!-- / line length and height section --}}



      <section id="section-contrast-and-accessibility" class="site-section">
        <h3 class="hca-text--title">Contrast &amp; Accessibility</h3>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-5">
            <div class="site-container--body-content">
              <p class="hca-text--body-1">A text color that is too similar to the background color is hard to read. Text with too much contrast can also be hard to read (for example, for readers with dyslexia). This is especially true of light-colored text against dark backgrounds.</p>

              <p class="hca-text--body-1">WCAG 2.0 level AA requires a contrast ratio of 4.5:1 for normal text and 3:1 for large text. Level AAA requires a contrast ratio of 7:1 for normal text and 4.5:1 for large text. Large text is defined as 14 point (typically 18.66px) and bold or larger, or 18 point (typically 24px) or larger.</p>

              <p class="hca-text--body-1">Our color combinations also consider contrast ratios for users who perceive color differently.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-7">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-sm-6">
                <div class="site-card hca-background--white">
                  <span class="hca-text--subhead hca-text__color--asphalt">Asphalt on White</span>
                </div>
                <small class="hca-text--support">Contrast ratio: 15.34:1</small>

                <br /><br />

                <div class="site-card hca-background--steam">
                  <span class="hca-text--subhead hca-text__color--asphalt">Asphalt on Steam</span>
                </div>
                <small class="hca-text--support">Contrast ratio: 14.28:1</small>

                <br /><br />

                <div class="site-card hca-background--geyser">
                  <span class="hca-text--subhead hca-text__color--asphalt">Asphalt on Geyser</span>
                </div>
                <small class="hca-text--support">Contrast ratio: 11.25:1</small>

                <br /><br />

                <div class="site-card hca-background--slate">
                  <span class="hca-text--subhead hca-text__color--asphalt">Asphalt on Slate</span>
                </div>
                <small class="hca-text--support">Contrast ratio: 4.87:1</small>

                <br /><br />
              </div>

              <div class="col-sm-6">
                <div class="site-card hca-background--white">
                  <span class="hca-text--subhead">Cadet on White</span>
                </div>
                <small class="hca-text--support">Contrast ratio: 7.69:1</small>

                <br /><br />

                <div class="site-card hca-background--steam">
                  <span class="hca-text--subhead">Cadet on Steam</span>
